[30;1m8 | [0m[35m## Semantic versioning[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mWe try to follow [semantic versioning](https://semver.org) with our versioning scheme.[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mThis scheme breaks down a version number into `{major.minor.point}` sections.[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35mAt a `point` release, there should be no changes beyond bug fixes.[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35m`minor` releases can include new features.[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35m`major` releases can break old APIs.[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m28 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m30 | [0m[35mWhen a minor release is made, a release branch should be cut and pushed to the main repo (e.g. `1.7.[0m
[30;1m31 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35mFor PRs which fix an bug in the most recent minor release, the changes will need to added to both th[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35mTo accomplish this, PRs which fix bugs are assigned a patch version milestone such as `1.7.4`.[0m

[30;1m56 | [0m[35m### Performance[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m58 | [0m[35mIt's more important that you're accurately testing the code works than it is that test suite runs qu[0m
[30;1m59 | [0m[35mThat said, it's nice when the test suite runs fast.[0m
[30;1m60 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m61 | [0m[35mYou can check how long tests take to run by passing `--durations=0` argument to `pytest`.[0m
[30;1m62 | [0m[35mHopefully your new tests won't show up on top![0m
